	       "-0.0" constant is NaN, a self-reproducing FIXED-POINT bug in the bootstrap tcc lineage,
	       which poisons (-0.0)-x — i.e. EVERY float negation, compile-time AND runtime. Build -0.0
	       from its IEEE bit pattern via integer ops (which tcc-0.9.26 compiles correctly), breaking
